children.name: After having received the brief and done subsequent future trend research, we established key objectives, our "north stars," to guide our efforts. These goals included a primary focus on sustainability, delving beyond the use of eco-friendly materials to incorporate sustainable practices and a forward-thinking business model. The autonomous capabilities of modern vehicles captured our attention as a gateway to innovative sensory interactions, prompting us to delve into this realm. Additionally, we drew inspiration from the concept of the Cupra tribe, aspiring to reimagine its essence for the years 2030-2035, specifically exploring avenues that do not rely on traditional vehicle ownership as a prerequisite for tribal membership.
children.characters:
After having received the brief and done subsequent future trend research, we established key objectives, our "north stars," to guide our efforts.

 These goals included a primary focus on sustainability, delving beyond the use of eco-friendly materials to incorporate sustainable practices and a forward-thinking business model.

 The autonomous capabilities of modern vehicles captured our attention as a gateway to innovative sensory interactions, prompting us to delve into this realm. 

Additionally, we drew inspiration from the concept of the Cupra tribe, aspiring to reimagine its essence for the years 2030-2035, specifically exploring avenues that do not rely on traditional vehicle ownership as a prerequisite for tribal membership.

children.name: Sustainability: A central value integral to our concept and our target audience is sustainability. This encompasses sustainable consumption, usage practices, and the choice of brands they engage with. That's why we envision the car as part of a carpooling service facilitated by Cupra. By grounding our concept in a model like car sharing with carpooling, we anticipate enhanced and more efficient utilization of the cars. This approach allows Cupra to exert a comprehensive impact on the entire lifecycle of the vehicles, enabling repairs, refurbishments, and recycling. Connecting people to the Cupra experience, not just the vehicle, we believe this model fosters a connection to the brand and its vehicles without the necessity of ownership. Enabling connections The experience we aimed to create revolves around embracing connections and the present moment, recognizing the increasing importance of such connections. Embracing the passengers’ full identities Looking ahead, the fusion of our physical and digital identities is inevitable. We view this as a significant opportunity to leverage these intertwined identities for diverse experiences and to distinguish our brand.

children.name: Let’s introduce you to our concept: The interior is made for 4 people. The Interior is capable of changing between the driving and autonomous orientations. With the sliding of the lower seat the passengers can face the right direction of driving or face the other passengers. Each individual is surrounded by a personal envelope which is a space for his digital twin can manifest, these 4 enveloping surfaces are enclosed in a collaborative canvas running around the entire interior. The collaborative and individual canvases visually represent the personal identities of users and serve as a layer to facilitate and highlight the atmosphere between passengers after they have given consent to the car. The smart seatbelt plays a pivotal role in connecting the user and the car, serving as a direct communication channel. The tribe members wear a hand wearable .This wearable stores the individual’s digital identity and serves as a medium through which users provide consent and request control through movement. It enables intentional and direct interaction with the car, and the haptic feedback from the wearable acts as a reminder and confirmation for ongoing interactions. And finally there is a discreet UI layer to give the essential information about the ride. Each element varies in expressivity based on the context of use.

children.name: After the introduction, this is the point of connection . As the person secures their seatbelt, they touch their chest and take a deep breath. They sense a gentle pull from the seatbelt, providing physical reassurance that the car is ready to safeguard them. By placing their hand on their heart, they experience a heartbeat sensation on both the seatbelt and the wearable device. It's as if the car acknowledges their presence and willingness to engage. This initiates the individual canvas, capturing real-time data and prompting the user to tune into their inner emotions

children.name: While enjoying the autonomous ride they can relax and really embrace the environment. When looking around them they can observe the dynamic creature they are sitting in. The body panels are Dark blue with mat texture and this gives a deep submersed feeling. Hiding inside them is mild ambient lighting. On their sides they see the skeleton of the car. This structure coming out of the central heart has a fabric like texture. The texture is inspired by fungal surface and will try to mimic the sinneuy texture of mushrooms. The skeleton has orangish coppery elements symbolising the nervous system of the interior, housing all the technology, sensors and projectors. In front of them and on the outside of the alcoves they see some soft, translucent felt like surfaces that serves as projection canvases evoking a sort of translucent skin. It is made up of soft but structurally rigid surface and these surfaces invite the look of the passenger, as there are different elements showing at different times. This is also where they see the UI giving them discreet indications on the driving of the car. And the UI being in this greenish blue colour and being reflected on the translucent canvas gives a feel of mysterious blood coming from the car. The whole environment evokes a feeling of being part of a mysterious entity that can be interacted with in a subtle way.

children.name: We envision the sharing and influence of various things, with music being a prime example. It serves as a great way to initiate interaction and connect with people we may not have known previously. Think of the sense of kinship you feel at a concert. Cupra physarum can enhance this experience by understanding passengers' music preferences through shared algorithms. It then provides fitting music recommendations. As each person's music contributes to a collective canvas, it encourages further conversation.

children.name: Keeping the connection to automotive heritage the ability to enjoy driving is still available, and can be requested bu the driver. to do so they need to ask consent of the car and the other passengers, and they do that by touching their heart, this gives them a haptic feedback on their hand, and the collective canvas will show that their is a change of atmosphere, asking other people if they consent to the change of experience, once they have given consent by also touching their heart. The driver will get a hand feeback letting them know that they will soon be in charge, and every passenger’s seatbelt will give a tug to let them know that the driving is starting now. The collective canvas will them become more calm to allow passengers to really focus on the outside environment and the feeling of the drive.

children.name: Preserving the automotive legacy, drivers can request permission to take control for an immersive driving experience. By touching their heart, drivers signal their desire, receiving haptic feedback. The collective canvas signals the atmosphere shift, prompting passengers to consent by touching their hearts. Once granted, the driver receives confirmation, and seatbelts gently tug, signaling the start of the drive. The collective canvas then calms, enabling passengers to fully immerse in the journey and surroundings.

children.name: Then the joy of driving is taking a new form. The person in charge will steer the car with their hand. (add the movement and what they do). While the person is driving, the car will allow for the other passengers to also really connect with the journey. And this is done by some pressure through the seatbelt. When they are turning right or left, they can feel the turning of the car. and when it is speeding up, the seatbelt will hold them tighter to enhance the feeling of acceleration. As if they are collectively feeling what the car is feeling.

children.name: In the video we just shared, we focused on three main ideas, which served as our guiding principles or "north stars" throughout the design process. These ideas represent our understanding of the project brief. Firstly, we delved into the concept of a tribe formed on the road. The inspiration for this came from Cupra's presentation on the notion of a Cupra tribe. This sparked our curiosity to explore ways of fostering a sense of kinship through shared experiences. Next, we investigated the potential for shared sensory experiences. Level 4th autonomous driving technology introduces new possibilities for interactions. We aimed to navigate this space to create immersive and meaningful experiences. Lastly, it was crucial for our entire concept to align with a future world where circular production methods and sustainable consumption and usage practices are widespread. Our goal is to contribute to a world where these practices are the norm.

Lastly, it was crucial for our entire concept to align with a future world where circular production methods and sustainable consumption and usage practices are widespread. Our goal is to contribute to a world where these practices are the norm.
